<td valign="top" width="263"> <p style="line-height: 1.3em; color: #00253e; font-size: 14px; margin-top: 0; font-family: Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif;"><span style="color: #000000;"><strong><a href="https://www.datacenterknowledge.com/regulation/china-weighs-letting-us-cloud-providers-operate-their-own-data-centers" target="_blank" id="" style="color: #000000;">China weights lettings US cloud providers operate their own data centers</a> (Data Center Knowledge):</strong>&nbsp;This could be a significant change, although the details (and there are many of them) are still unclear. But cloud providers and customers alike might prefer getting rid of the local telco middle-man in these engagements.&nbsp;</span></p> </td> 
